node.text:
What does "well within" mean to you? 💛 The answer is different for everyone, but there is one common thread: it all starts with *connection* ...a connection to your mind, your body, your spirit, to each other.

So after a brief retreat hiatus, we're bringing everyone back together for something we've never done before. It's called Well Within. You just got to meet some of the speakers. As for the activities, you'll be able to choose from a menu of exciting breakout sessions and workshops:

✨  Guided meditations
✨  Yoga + movement classes
✨  Breathwork
✨  Sound bowl healings
✨  Kirtan (call and response chanting)
✨  Yoga nidra (meditative relaxation)
✨  Self-abhyanga (self-massage)
✨  Medical Vedic (eastern) astrology
✨  Somatic therapy
✨  Immersive Energy Healing
✨  Recapitulation exercises
✨  Musical healing performance and free-form movement
✨  Lessons from Deepak Chopra + other Mind-Body Health Experts
...and more!

Meet us on the California coast October 29-31 and find your wellness within. You can learn more at http://chopra.com/retreats/well-within

node.text:
Loss is inevitable. And there is no one-size-fits-all approach to healing. 💛 As an alternative to repressing, numbing, or spiritual bypassing your emotion, here are some ways you can bring awareness to your grief and use feeling for healing:

1. Journal. Document your feelings. Acknowledge the things that hurt you, even if you don't want to.

2. Talk. If grieving a loss, express your love for them. Hold space for them in your heart. Even write them a letter.

3. Meditate. Chödrön writes in When Things Fall Apart, “Meditation is an invitation to notice when we reach our limits and to not get carried away by hope and fear. Through meditation, we’re able to see clearly what’s going on with our thoughts and emotions, and we can also let them go.”

Today, we're celebrating 🎉 each one of you helping us hit the big 1M followers. Here's some of (y)our favorite moments from the past few years. We wake up and go to sleep each day with your comments, questions, likes and dislikes, shares, and DMs and we're sure of it – we have the rawest, realest, and most committed audience in this space. Thank you for trusting us as your guide and for sharing the most vulnerable of moments with us as we all create this meaningful community in our shared search for truth and spiritual growth. It's a blessing and surely an honor. 🙇‍♀️

With love, the Chopra team
